#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.93"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.93:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.93:0.2"
msgid "10. Pupphavagga"
msgstr "10. Flowers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.93:0.3"
msgid "93. Nadīsutta"
msgstr "93. A River"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.138"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.93:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

#. VAR: ubhosu tīresu → ubhato tīre (si) | ubhato tīresu (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: pabbajā → babbajā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.93:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, nadī pabbateyyā ohārinī dūraṅgamā sīghasotā. Tassā "
"ubhosu tīresu kāsā cepi jātā assu, te naṃ ajjholambeyyuṃ; kusā cepi jātā "
"assu, te naṃ ajjholambeyyuṃ; pabbajā cepi jātā assu, te naṃ ajjholambeyyuṃ; "
"bīraṇā cepi jātā assu, te naṃ ajjholambeyyuṃ; rukkhā cepi jātā assu, te naṃ "
"ajjholambeyyuṃ. Tassā puriso sotena vuyhamāno kāse cepi gaṇheyya, te "
"palujjeyyuṃ. So tatonidānaṃ anayabyasanaṃ āpajjeyya. Kuse cepi gaṇheyya, "
"pabbaje cepi gaṇheyya, bīraṇe cepi gaṇheyya, rukkhe cepi gaṇheyya, te "
"palujjeyyuṃ. So tatonidānaṃ anayabyasanaṃ āpajjeyya."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose, mendicants, there was a mountain river that flowed swiftly, going "
"far, carrying all before it. If wild sugarcane, kusa grass, reeds, vetiver, "
"or trees grew on either bank, they’d overhang the river. And if a person who "
"was being swept along by the current grabbed the wild sugarcane, kusa grass, "
"reeds, vetiver, or trees, it’d break off, and they’d come to ruin because of "
"that."

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.3"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa "
"akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa "
"akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto "
msgstr ""
"In the same way, an uneducated ordinary person has not seen the noble ones, "
"and is neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’"
"ve not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the "
"teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.4"
msgid ""
"rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā rūpaṃ, rūpasmiṃ "
"vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form."

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.5"
msgid "Tassa taṃ rūpaṃ palujjati."
msgstr "But their form breaks off,"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.6"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr "and they come to ruin because of that."

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.7"
msgid "Vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "They regard feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.8"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.9"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.10"
msgid ""
"viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā viññāṇaṃ, "
"viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, "
"or self in consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.11"
msgid "Tassa taṃ viññāṇaṃ palujjati."
msgstr "But their consciousness breaks off,"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.12"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr "and they come to ruin because of that."

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.13"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.14"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.15"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” …"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.16"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.17"
msgid "“Vedanā …"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.18"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.19"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.20"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.21"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.22"
msgid "“Tasmātiha … pe …"
msgstr "“So you should truly see …"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.23"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Seeing this …"

msgctxt "sn22.93:1.24"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.93:1.25"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
